FM
Cross-platform file manager (Tauri + Vue + Rust)

STATUS
This project is an active work-in-progress.
It is already usable for core navigation and selection workflows, but it is not complete.
Some features are intentionally scaffolded for future expansion.

IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT AUTHORSHIP
This codebase was built with strong AI assistance and rapid iteration.
The implementation quality is real, but development speed does not represent a traditional manual timeline.
This README is intentionally direct and honest about that.

PROJECT GOALS
1) Fast, predictable UI with no filesystem work on the renderer thread.
2) Native-like desktop behavior while still using web UI technology.
3) A reusable backend core that can evolve independently of the current UI.

ARCHITECTURE
Frontend:
- Vue + Vite, rendered inside Tauri webview.
- Focused on state rendering and interaction logic.
- Uses commands/events for backend communication.

Backend:
- Rust (Tauri commands + async tasks).
- Owns filesystem operations, chunked directory reading, cancellation, storage bootstrap, and platform integration.

State and persistence:
- Preferences via tauri-plugin-store.
- Queryable data/history via SQLite (rusqlite).
- Paths and storage bootstrapped in OS-specific config locations.

CURRENT FEATURE SET
Navigation:
- Back/forward/up navigation.
- Address bar with breadcrumb navigation.
- Address bar edit mode with manual path navigation.
- Unix path expansion support in address bar (for example: ~, $HOME).

Virtual locations:
- fm://welcome (home/start screen)
- fm://home (alias to fm://welcome)
- fm://trash

Views:
- List view and grid view.
- Per-directory view mode persistence.

Listing engine:
- Chunked directory listing from Rust.
- Cancellation of in-flight read jobs on navigation.
- Hidden file detection and toggle (Ctrl+H).
- File icon loading with caching.

Selection:
- Single selection.
- Ctrl/Cmd multi-select.
- Shift range-select.
- Rectangle selection.
- Ctrl + rectangle toggle behavior.
- Keyboard cursor tracking.
- Ctrl+Arrow movement without clearing selection.
- Space toggles focused item selection.
- Shift+Arrow and Ctrl+Shift+Arrow range behavior.
- Ctrl+A select all.

File operations:
- Open file/folder on activation.
- Rename (F2, inline).
- New file draft flow from sidebar quick add.
- New folder draft flow (Ctrl+Shift+N).
- Delete with native confirmation.
- Delete routes to OS trash by default.
- Shift+Delete permanent delete.
- Trash view listing.
- Empty Trash action (Linux/Windows path currently implemented).

Context menus:
- Native context menu framework for file area.
- Distinguishes right-click context:
  empty space, file, folder.
- Current menu actions are placeholder/informational by design.

UI:
- Resizable sidebar.
- Welcome/start page with user dirs and drives.
- Action toolbar.
- Status bar:
  item count, selected count, selected size (files-only selection).
- Address bar style customized toward native segmented breadcrumb look.

PLATFORM NOTES
Linux:
- Primary development platform.
- Trash flow and listing integrated.

Windows:
- Core navigation/listing/selection logic is cross-platform.
- Delete-to-trash supported via trash crate abstraction.
- Trash listing/empty behavior may differ and needs platform validation.

macOS:
- Core app should run via Tauri stack.
- Some trash maintenance flows are intentionally deferred for mac-specific implementation.

KNOWN LIMITATIONS / TODO
- Context menu actions are placeholders (framework first, actions later).
- Copy/cut/paste pipeline is not fully wired end-to-end yet.
- Advanced conflict handling for move/copy not implemented.
- No dedicated transfer queue UI yet.
- No full search subsystem yet.
- Drag/drop move/copy behavior not finalized.
- Trash restore flow not implemented yet.

LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
Requirements:
- Node.js and npm
- Rust toolchain
- Tauri prerequisites for your OS

Install:
- npm install

Run (frontend + tauri dev):
- npm run tauri dev

Frontend only:
- npm run dev

Build frontend:
- npm run build

PROJECT LAYOUT
- src/                  Vue app
- src/components/       UI components
- src/lib/              Frontend services/utilities
- src-tauri/src/        Rust backend
- src-tauri/src/core.rs Core listing/walk/cancellation logic
- src-tauri/src/context_menu.rs Native file-area context menu framework

DESIGN PRINCIPLES USED
- Keep renderer lightweight.
- Stream and incrementally render.
- Cancel stale jobs aggressively.
- Prioritize keyboard and native desktop interaction patterns.
- Prefer modular services over monolithic App-level logic.

CONTRIBUTING STYLE (PRACTICAL)
- Keep changes incremental and testable.
- Avoid giant mixed-purpose patches when possible.
- Preserve current UX consistency unless intentionally redesigning.
- For file operations, keep backend safety checks strict.

